  "commentary": "With SPX at 6811.59 trading below the GEX flip at 6867, dealers are in positive gamma territory and will sell any rally toward the 6850-6900 resistance zone where massive +5.38B in gamma sits. The strong positive GEX walls from 6850-7000 create a natural ceiling, while the -1.58B negative gamma pocket at 6755 provides downside support where dealers would aggressively buy dips. Key levels to watch: 6867 flip line as the regime pivot, 6900 max positive gamma as the primary sell zone, and 6755 as the buy-the-dip magnet.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pulled back toward 6850-6867 with limited upside above 6900.",
